description:
When using ClassTypeLoader to load an Interface Type with getter methods defined the resulting *MetadataType* contains inexistent fields


For example having an Interface Animal like this one:
{code:java}
public interface Animal 
{
    String getSpeciesName();
}
{code}

The resulting MetadataType will contain a field named "speciesName"

Right now the MessageHandler's handle method is defined as:
{code:java}
    /**
     * Handles the {@code message} and notifies the result using the given {@code completionHandler}
     *
     * @param message           the {@link MuleMessage} to be handled
     * @param completionHandler the {@link CompletionHandler} on which the result is to be notified
     */
    //TODO: MULE-8946: this should actually receive a messaging exception
    void handle(MuleMessage<Payload, Attributes> message,
                                      CompletionHandler<MuleMessage<Payload, Attributes>, Exception> completionHandler);
{code}
which basically means a Source should produce and expect the same "kind" of MuleMessage since the payload and attributes type must be the same for the message and completionHandler. This is wrong since nothing can be assumed about the flow's result.

