The problem is that Extensions API is not resolving the full list of parameters that the method requires. Is only resolving 2 parameters. For all those which value is null it's doing nothing.

Consider the following code: 

{code:java}
@Parameter
@Optional
private DestinationType destinationType = new QueueDestinationType();
{code}

If the paremeter had some specific optional value, it would make sense for the QueuDestinationType created there to be overriden. However, if it defaults to null, it's not from a UX perspective to force the user into implementing Initialisable and doing the check/initialisation there. That value should be respected when the optional is null.

