When trying to call the method: addMessageProcessorPathElements
In a ForEach object that has not been init the method fails with:

{code}
Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: fromIndex(1) > toIndex(0)
	at java.util.ArrayList.subListRangeCheck(ArrayList.java:964)
	at java.util.ArrayList.subList(ArrayList.java:954)
	at org.mule.routing.Foreach.addMessageProcessorPathElements(Foreach.java:143)
{code}

The reason for it is that, foreach is expecting to be initialised at this time, thus having at least 3 MP. 

{code}
        List<MessageProcessor> mps = getOwnedMessageProcessors().subList(1, getOwnedMessageProcessors().size() - 1);
{code}

When not init the for each only contains those MP defined in the XML with out the splitter and the filter. So in the event the for each only contains 1 mp it fails. 

The class ForEach should validate the size of the list, or at least know if it has been init in order not to fail.

